Title: tryBase58Decode
Description: Like base58Decode but returns an empty string in case of error.
encoded: String or FixedString. If the string is not a valid Base58-encoded value, returns an empty string in case of error.
A string containing the decoded value of the argument.
Examples: SELECT tryBase58Decode('3dc8KtHrwM') as res, tryBase58Decode('invalid') as res_invalid;
EffectiveSQLsRefined: SELECT tryBase58Decode('3dc8KtHrwM') as res, tryBase58Decode('invalid') as res_invalid;
